This is a classic Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use (TOCTOU) vulnerability. Checking a file's existence and then acting on that check creates a race condition window that attackers can exploit.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"io"
	"net/http"
	"os"
	"path/filepath"
)

func uploadHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
	filename := r.FormValue("filename")
	uploadPath := filepath.Join("/uploads", filename)

